rule: Before planning or applying any code changes, thoroughly analyze the current folder and file structure. 

steps:
  - Inspect the overall directory tree to identify the purpose of each major folder.
  - Locate the canonical data model definitions and architectural documents.
  - Identify domain boundaries (frontend, backend, infra, intelligence) and restrict changes to appropriate domains.
  - Reference any relevant README, AGENTS.md, or tasks files for architectural intent.
  - Ensure you do not make breaking changes to the folder structure or move critical files without explicit instruction.
  - If any structure or placement is unclear, pause and ask for clarification before proceeding.
  - Your task planning must conform to the established organization in the repo; do not create new folders or files in root unless required.
  - Always respect protected files and documented folder conventions (see `.cursor/rules/folder-structure.mdc` and project PRD).

